File: The rand is now 40 percent weaker to the US dollar compared to the same time last year. JOHANNESBURG - The rand has hit a new all-time low on Friday. It's now 40 percent weaker to the US dollar compared to the same time last year. The local currency is one of many emerging markets currencies hit by the investor panic of the COVID-19 pandemic. READ: Rand plunges to record low after junk status But domestically, the rand is also under pressure following Moody’s downgrade of South Africa to subinvestment grade last week. A weaker rand will make imports more expensive and stoke inflation.